    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Most Linux terminals that I've used bind paste to something else, since C-v is used so often. \n\nRegarding alt, if you're referring to the way it adds accents to characters on OS X, most people either rebind it to meta in the terminal, or use ESC. \n\nI'm not sure if it was clear, but these are standard emacs keybindings. It's very reasonable to expect emacs mode to use them, especially if page up/down perform such an important action. Does the vi mode use whatever vi's page up/down bindings are?\n"
  },
