    "created_at": "2016-07-06T10:06:55Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-07-06T10:06:55Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Ctrl-V is already bound to paste on Windows systems, and I can imagine we may want to bind it to some form of paste on other systems at some point. I'm sure I accidentally press Ctrl-V instead of Ctrl-Shift-V in my terminal sometimes.\n\nI'm not sure that we can capture meta key combos - PTK doesn't appear to expose any combos with a meta key modifier.\n\nWhile the mode is called emacs, I think the vast majority of users are coming to it from the default readline key bindings, and are more likely to be confused than helped by closely emulating emacs. I agree that if emacs users want lots of their shortcuts, we should possibly offer a separate mode for that and rename the default. (Ping @jonathanslenders )\n"
  },
